						<summary>

						<p>This is damaged and is not dated. It records (that the <hi rend="bold">Āḷupa</hi> king) <hi rend="bold">Raṇasāgara</hi> made a gift to <hi rend="bold">Nāgamma</hi> of <hi rend="bold">Kayra-vaṁśa,</hi> who was as brave as Mahēndra, for crushing the army of <hi rend="bold">Pāybaya.</hi> The characters of the record belong to the 8th century A.D.</p>						

